article.description: — Eddy Kayouloud and Camren Hunter scored 18 points apiece and Darious Hall added a double-double to lead Central Arkansas to a 93-88 victory over Lipscomb in Atlantic Sun Conference action on Sunday.
article.headline: Kayouloud, Hunter, Hall lead Central Arkansas past Lipscomb
article.linkText: Kayouloud, Hunter, Hall lead Central Arkansas past Lipscomb
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- — Eddy Kayouloud and Camren Hunter scored 18 points apiece and Darious Hall added a double-double to lead Central Arkansas to a 93-88 victory over Lipscomb in Atlantic Sun Conference action on Sunday. Hall finished with 16 points, 10 rebounds and seven assists for the Bears (5-10, 2-0). Jared Chatham had 11 points as Central Arkansas won its fourth straight game at home. Ahsan Asadullah scored a season-high 32 points with 11 rebounds and five assists for the Bisons (8-9, 1-1). KJ Johnson added 13 points and seven assists.
